{"event_id": "7adc1d77-57e2-420f-b7fb-883f1a75507c", "trace_id": "b66bfb7b15b1442e", "session_id": "9a5d4cc4", "timestamp": "2026-05-05T11:50:28.213045+00:00", "tool": "filesystem.write_file", "args_hash": "dda01586b5fc78bf0a445971d5e086df1e982d85a1fcf390b5283eb11fe9351a", "args_redacted": {"raw": {"path": "workspace/ssh_summary.txt", "content": "SSH Security Best Practices Summary\n====================================\n\n1. KEY-BASED AUTHENTICATION\n   - Use Ed25519 keys (preferred): ssh-keygen -t ed25519\n   - RSA 4096-bit as fallback: ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096\n   - Avoid DSA and ECDSA keys\n   - Protect private keys with strong passphrases\n   - Use ssh-agent or hardware tokens (YubiKey)\n\n2. DISABLE PASSWORD AUTHENTICATION\n   - Set 'PasswordAuthentication no' in sshd_config\n   - Set 'ChallengeResponseAuthentication no'\n   - Eliminates brute-force password attacks\n\n3. DISABLE ROOT LOGIN\n   - Set 'PermitRootLogin no' in sshd_config\n   - Use sudo/su for privilege escalation\n\n4. RESTRICT USER ACCESS\n   - Use AllowUsers or AllowGroups directives\n   - Example: AllowUsers alice bob\n\n5. STRONG CRYPTOGRAPHY\n   - KexAlgorithms: curve25519-sha256, diffie-hellman-group16-sha512\n   - Ciphers: chacha20-poly1305@openssh.com, aes256-gcm@openssh.com\n   - MACs: hmac-sha2-256-etm@openssh.com, hmac-sha2-512-etm@openssh.com\n\n6. CHANGE DEFAULT PORT\n   - Use non-standard port (e.g., 2222) to reduce bot scans\n\n7. FIREWALL RATE LIMITING\n   - Restrict SSH to trusted IPs when possible\n   - Use iptables/nftables rate limiting\n\n8. FAIL2BAN\n   - Install and configure fail2ban to block repeated failures\n\n9. DISABLE UNNECESSARY FEATURES\n   - X11Forwarding no (unless needed)\n   - AllowTcpForwarding no (unless needed)\n   - PermitTunnel no (unless needed)\n\n10. REGULAR UPDATES\n    - Keep OpenSSH updated\n    - Subscribe to security advisories\n\n11. TWO-FACTOR AUTHENTICATION (2FA)\n    - Add 2FA via PAM (libpam-google-authenticator)\n    - Provides additional layer beyond SSH keys\n\n12. AUDIT LOGGING\n    - Set LogLevel VERBOSE in sshd_config\n    - Monitor /var/log/auth.log regularly\n    - Consider centralized logging (SIEM)\n\n13. CLIENT-SIDE HARDENING\n    - Use ~/.ssh/config with strict settings per host\n    - Set 'VerifyHostKeyDNS yes' for DNSSEC validation\n    - Use SSH certificates for large-scale deployments\n\n14. IDLE TIMEOUT\n    - Set 'ClientAliveInterval 300' (5 minutes)\n    - Set 'ClientAliveCountMax 0' to disconnect idle sessions\n\n15. MAX AUTHENTICATION ATTEMPTS\n    - Set 'MaxAuthTries 3' to limit attempts per connection\n\n16. BANNER WARNING\n    - Set 'Banner /etc/issue.net' with legal warning\n\nREFERENCES:\n- OpenSSH manual: https://www.openssh.com/manual.html\n- CIS Benchmarks for SSH\n- NIST SP 800-123\n- Mozilla OpenSSH Security Guide\n"}}, "input_labels": {"SI": "SI:MED", "DS": "DS:SENSITIVE"}, "policy_decision": "ALLOW", "matched_rule": "", "rule_reason": "No matching rule; allowed", "prev_event_hash": "9c14213339fa8772c1ba615dd2c5466eb53fdcc32117468f187872cec69368b8", "event_hash": "83a9908f730153aa3d5483d56ed5712b0f4c050629d6e7e3c6582c655fb29132"}
